        <abstract>
            <p>Thanks CD for notes concerning the development of his ideas about the origin of species. Says August Schleicher and Carl Gegenbaur also interested.</p>
            <p>Names new supporters of CD’s theory, including Max Schultze, Rudolf Leuckart, and Alexander Braun. Zoologists have been more interested than botanists.</p> 
<p>He is writing a general work on the relationships among animals [<hi rend="italic">Generelle Morphologie der Organismen</hi> (1866)].</p>  
<p>Comments on Fritz Müller’s <hi rend="italic">Für Darwin</hi> [1864].</p>  
<p>Gegenbaur is revising his <hi rend="italic">Grundzüge der vergleichenden Anatomie</hi> [2d ed. (1870)] to accord with evolution.</p>  
<p>Thanks CD for copy of book on balanids [<hi rend="italic">Living Cirripedia</hi>, vol. 2].</p> 
        </abstract>
